01:17:10.800 --> 01:17:16.960
My student said he hated change, but

01:17:14.119 --> 01:17:19.439
through writing in his journal all year

01:17:16.960 --> 01:17:23.600
and finishing 236 handwritten pages,

01:17:19.439 --> 01:17:26.079
he decided he accepts change and he loves
it. So, I thought, I am going to

01:17:23.600 --> 01:17:30.199
he decided he accepts change and he loves
it. So, I thought, I'm going to

01:17:28.079 --> 01:17:33.920
start with that about change and it
reminded me

01:17:31.640 --> 01:17:38.199
of where I started, opportunity for
change.

01:17:35.760 --> 01:17:40.480
And that's what Brookline means to me

01:17:38.199 --> 01:17:43.519
and Bob, you helped start that

01:17:40.479 --> 01:17:46.039
before I got there, but Brookline

01:17:43.520 --> 01:17:48.480
made a great program for

01:17:46.039 --> 01:17:50.920
students who needed it.

01:17:48.479 --> 01:17:54.520
They made a family of teachers with Bill
Grady, Bill Hibbert, Jack

01:17:53.239 --> 01:17:59.720
Liss, Eileen Lombardi, and many other

01:17:57.119 --> 01:18:01.319
great people. Bob Gray helped us

01:17:59.720 --> 01:18:05.480
from the town.

01:18:01.319 --> 01:18:08.679
It created a wonderful feeling of

01:18:05.479 --> 01:18:12.320
family, consistency, clarity, and
relationships

01:18:10.359 --> 01:18:17.119
that I have continued for all of

01:18:14.479 --> 01:18:20.239
these 31 years. It is

01:18:17.119 --> 01:18:23.439
a calling. The poetry festival with Lynn

01:18:20.239 --> 01:18:26.279
Cohen and all of the librarians

01:18:23.439 --> 01:18:28.599
