01:18:26.279 --> 01:18:33.079
It's all teamwork. It's all family, with
everyone sharing their stories,

01:18:30.680 --> 01:18:36.240
like Geraldine Mondy and her siblings
telling their stories and

01:18:33.079 --> 01:18:39.920
my friends in the English Department, and
Ed Weiser, who I went to graduate school

01:18:36.239 --> 01:18:43.119
with. Remember our project on technology?
I started by

01:18:41.680 --> 01:18:47.199
talking about handwriting in the journal.

01:18:45.680 --> 01:18:50.463
And so, um [laughter]

01:18:48.439 --> 01:18:54.479
it's the best technology there is. But, um

01:18:51.640 --> 01:18:57.639
to keep it short, I just want to say

01:18:55.600 --> 01:18:59.680
Brookline public schools are a

01:18:57.640 --> 01:19:02.880
wonderful family. We take care of our

01:18:59.680 --> 01:19:06.440
children. We take care of our staff. And

01:19:02.880 --> 01:19:08.199
I love the teamwork, and I'm forever
thankful for these years. And

01:19:06.439 --> 01:19:12.439
I am not done yet. I'm not done. I'm still
young. My mom is 86. Sorry, Mom.

01:19:10.680 --> 01:19:17.319
And she still works. So, alright.

01:19:15.079 --> 01:19:18.159
[laughter] I love you. Thank you very much
to

01:19:17.319 --> 01:19:22.639
my whole team, and to everyone here today.
Thank you.

01:19:20.840 --> 01:19:26.545
[applause]

01:19:24.524 --> 01:19:26.545
Thank you, Ally. Ed Weiser, you're next.

01:19:30.079 --> 01:19:35.399
Thank you. Thank you. [applause] Um yeah,
good evening. Thank you for

01:19:37.199 --> 01:19:43.399
celebrating with all of us. Thank you for
staying for the last person to

01:19:41.960 --> 01:19:46.679
speak. Um and um so, this is going to be

01:19:45.680 --> 01:19:50.640
go. Um and um so, this is going to be

01:19:49.119 --> 01:19:55.480
I thank the Brookline community,
especially the Brookline Education Foundation (BEF).

01:19:53.920 --> 01:19:59.119
If I could go back thirty years and tell
myself that my teaching job would

01:19:57.319 --> 01:20:03.119
include skydiving, flying helicopters, and
later

01:20:00.520 --> 01:20:07.000
becoming an Emergency Medical Technician
(EMT), driving an ambulance on weekends,

01:20:05.560 --> 01:20:10.960
to teach students about the medical field,
I would not have believed it.

01:20:08.840 --> 01:20:13.199
I have had many adventures. Those I
mentioned

01:20:10.960 --> 01:20:16.119
were all supported by the BEF.

01:20:13.199 --> 01:20:18.079
For one special experience, Bob, I don't
remember where the money

01:20:16.119 --> 01:20:20.640
came from for this. You might have helped,
but I went to a conference

01:20:19.359 --> 01:20:24.680
at the Fermi National Accelerator
Laboratory, a huge particle collider, in Illinois that summer,

01:20:22.159 --> 01:20:28.800
and I met Nobel Prize winner Leon
Lederman, and later started our first physics program

01:20:26.920 --> 01:20:32.360
for ninth graders.

01:20:30.199 --> 01:20:35.199
Brookline High School (BHS) became a
leader in helping more students take physics

01:20:32.359 --> 01:20:37.880
and other science classes.

01:20:35.199 --> 01:20:41.159
So much so that Jim Walsh,

01:20:40.000 --> 01:20:45.079
right there, surprised the Department of
Elementary and Secondary Education (DESE)

01:20:43.199 --> 01:20:49.479
because they created the Massachusetts
Comprehensive Assessment System (MCAS) exam for science,

01:20:47.439 --> 01:20:53.439
and he said, "You need to include
physics." People were shocked.

01:20:52.199 --> 01:20:57.719
Also, when Professor Lederman got a press
request,

01:20:55.359 --> 01:21:00.800
he would just send it to me because he was
too busy. That was a big honor.

01:20:59.239 --> 01:21:04.920
I was interviewed by the New York Times,
the Wall Street Journal, and more.

01:21:02.800 --> 01:21:07.399
Then after

01:21:06.399 --> 01:21:11.119
eleven years, Bob trusted me to lead the
science department.

01:21:08.840 --> 01:21:15.359
We created more opportunities for
students.

01:21:13.439 --> 01:21:17.639
We expanded the physical space of BHS for
the future.

01:21:15.359 --> 01:21:22.200
A real point of pride is being the leader
of the team that was often

01:21:20.039 --> 01:21:26.479
ranked among the top STEM schools in the
country.

01:21:24.039 --> 01:21:29.839
Our classrooms are now full of creativity,
inclusion, and hard work.

01:21:28.079 --> 01:21:32.920
I am very proud of that.

01:21:31.880 --> 01:21:38.720
During the building project, I asked for a
good budget for equipment,

01:21:36.560 --> 01:21:42.800
which included a medical simulation lab.
You can see three mannequins on the

01:21:40.600 --> 01:21:47.119
third floor of the STEM wing. They might
seem a bit strange,

01:21:44.840 --> 01:21:51.440
but they are useful.

01:21:49.960 --> 01:21:56.639
Sorry if they creep you out.

01:21:53.760 --> 01:21:58.960
One thing led to another and

01:21:56.640 --> 01:22:02.480
the BEF helped me become an EMT.

01:21:58.960 --> 01:22:03.840
Now I teach students how to figure out
what is wrong with Hal, not Mason, Hal the

01:22:02.479 --> 01:22:09.279
mannequin, when he comes to our emergency
department (ED) with

01:22:06.640 --> 01:22:13.599
shortness of breath and confusion.

01:22:12.000 --> 01:22:16.280
shortness of breath and altered mental
status.

01:22:14.760 --> 01:22:20.399
I stepped away from the leadership role.

01:22:17.840 --> 01:22:24.759
I wanted to grow the medical careers
offerings.

01:22:23.079 --> 01:22:28.560
I also added robotics, woodworking, and a
new construction class.

01:22:26.840 --> 01:22:32.240
I never thought this would happen when Bob
turned on the light.

01:22:30.479 --> 01:22:35.679
Do you remember that during my interview?

01:22:34.159 --> 01:22:38.880
You would turn the lights on and off.

01:22:37.039 --> 01:22:42.680
You asked the physics candidates to
explain what was happening.

01:22:41.079 --> 01:22:44.957
Very few people could explain the physics
of an alternating current circuit.

01:22:43.279 --> 01:22:49.600
I knew how to explain it. [laughter]

01:22:46.680 --> 01:22:53.560
In my last chapter here, I have a few more
years to go.

01:22:51.760 --> 01:22:57.600
I hope it will include an after-school
dual enrollment program for EMT certification.

01:22:55.520 --> 01:22:59.800
This will be with MassBay Community
College.

01:22:58.712 --> 01:23:04.359
[applause] Thank you. We have an initial
agreement.

01:23:02.880 --> 01:23:09.159
We just need a few more steps to make it
happen.

01:23:06.960 --> 01:23:13.639
