02:09:40.880 --> 02:09:47.159
In 1964, Brookline residents from a civil
rights group came to this committee.

02:09:45.520 --> 02:09:51.359
They said we need to help what is
happening in Boston.

02:09:49.159 --> 02:09:53.840
Most people do not know this.

02:09:51.359 --> 02:09:58.119
They think the events started in 1974 with
Judge Garrity.

02:09:56.399 --> 02:10:01.359
But it actually started in 1964.

02:10:00.520 --> 02:10:03.839
It is important to remember this history.

02:10:02.439 --> 02:10:08.079
In 1965, the president, now called the
chair, took action.

02:10:06.039 --> 02:10:11.199
He created a temporary committee.

02:10:09.479 --> 02:10:16.279
They worked with Boston and Brookline
civil rights activists.

02:10:13.920 --> 02:10:20.559
They helped create a program for students
to move from Boston to Brookline.

02:10:18.680 --> 02:10:21.720
In 1966, METCO was officially created.

02:10:20.560 --> 02:10:26.880
It filed papers with the state.

02:10:25.199 --> 02:10:30.760
By September 8th, 1966, it started running
with a grant.

02:10:29.159 --> 02:10:35.600
Later, it received state funding.

02:10:33.600 --> 02:10:38.400
In 1974, Brookline got its first METCO
director.

02:10:35.600 --> 02:10:41.039
I mention this because it is the same year
as the Judge Garrity decision.

02:10:38.399 --> 02:10:43.399
Some of the first METCO students, called
riders, have shared their stories.

02:10:41.039 --> 02:10:47.359
They say there was no one there
specifically to support them.

02:10:45.600 --> 02:10:51.880
They were just told to go to school.

02:10:50.159 --> 02:10:54.399
They had to get on the bus and go to
school alone.

02:10:51.880 --> 02:10:57.359
Pam King, a civil rights activist, talks
about this today.

02:10:54.399 --> 02:11:00.399
She is the daughter of Mel King.

02:10:59.199 --> 02:11:04.279
She says it would have been hard to send
her kids to METCO.

02:11:00.399 --> 02:11:07.839
She mentioned that it would have been
different if there had been a director.

02:11:04.279 --> 02:11:07.840
In 1974, Brookline also hired a
coordinator for Brookline High School.

02:11:07.920 --> 02:11:14.200
Gretchen Underwood became the METCO
coordinator in that year.

02:11:11.640 --> 02:11:16.920
We hope you see that over time,

02:11:15.800 --> 02:11:21.440
METCO and the town have really progressed.

02:11:20.319 --> 02:11:25.960
METCO. And then, not to pat myself on the
back cuz she's speaking about me

02:11:24.079 --> 02:11:28.880
metaphorically, she's saying, "But it
would have been different if we

02:11:26.960 --> 02:11:32.720
had a Malcolm." If there was a director.

02:11:31.079 --> 02:11:37.000
The same year we also hired a BHS
coordinator. So, uh that's, you know,

02:11:35.359 --> 02:11:41.640
one of the long-standing names in this
town through school, Gretchen Underwood,

02:11:39.079 --> 02:11:45.360
is that METCO coordinator in '74. And so,

02:11:43.000 --> 02:11:49.880
what I hope you'll see is, whoop, over
time, um

02:11:47.560 --> 02:11:52.120
we've really progressed with METCO as

02:11:49.880 --> 02:11:55.680
well as the town.

02:11:52.119 --> 02:11:58.680
Okay. Next slide please.

02:11:55.680 --> 02:12:00.240
Right now, we have 299 students.

02:11:58.680 --> 02:12:02.800
We can have 303 students.

02:12:00.239 --> 02:12:05.840
This number is set by the Department of
Elementary and Secondary Education (DESE).

02:12:02.800 --> 02:12:07.920
These students are in all 8 K-8 schools.
Some districts keep students in specific schools.

02:12:05.840 --> 02:12:10.840
They also go to Brookline High School
(BHS).

02:12:07.920 --> 02:12:13.000
We have 18 staff members right now.

02:12:10.840 --> 02:12:15.000
This includes an executive assistant, a
BHS coordinator,

02:12:13.000 --> 02:12:19.000
and an advisor, eight K-8 advisors, three
social workers, and three bus monitors.

02:12:16.880 --> 02:12:22.359
Keeping enough students is important for
our program's funding from DESE.

02:12:19.000 --> 02:12:25.600
To have the staff we need, we must keep
our student numbers high.

02:12:22.359 --> 02:12:28.759
If not, funding may be reduced, and we
won't serve METCO students properly.

02:12:25.600 --> 02:12:30.280
I will not read the vision now.

02:12:28.760 --> 02:12:33.279
One important goal of METCO is to promote
integration and diversity in many ways.

02:12:31.960 --> 02:12:38.039
This is not just about race, which was the
original goal.

02:12:35.800 --> 02:12:40.640
Originally, it was a desegregation
program.

02:12:38.039 --> 02:12:43.359
But now, METCO brings many kinds of
diversity.

02:12:40.640 --> 02:12:46.799
For example, Brookline's population has
changed a lot.

02:12:45.479 --> 02:12:49.720
Many of our METCO families represent
working-class, middle-class,

02:12:48.439 --> 02:12:52.320
and upper middle-class people of different
races who do not live in Brookline.

02:12:51.399 --> 02:12:56.519
Two years ago, Boston Magazine named
Boston's Black 100.

02:12:54.760 --> 02:12:58.920
Four of these were Brookline METCO
parents.

02:12:56.520 --> 02:13:01.960
These are not just METCO parents; they are
Brookline METCO parents.

02:12:58.920 --> 02:13:03.560
It is important to understand this.

02:13:01.960 --> 02:13:07.039
METCO brings religious, cultural, and
ethnic diversity to our district.

02:13:05.720 --> 02:13:11.720
Next slide, Betsy.

02:13:09.479 --> 02:13:13.559
But, METCO brings

02:13:11.720 --> 02:13:18.560
a host [snorts] of diverse things, and
I'll point out one.

02:13:16.840 --> 02:13:22.480
You know, the shifts in the town of
Brookline have shifted populations in a

02:13:20.800 --> 02:13:27.599
lot of ways. A lot of our METCO families

02:13:25.039 --> 02:13:29.479
represent

02:13:27.600 --> 02:13:34.039
working class, middle class, and even
upper middle class folks of race that

02:13:32.079 --> 02:13:36.519
don't necessarily live in the town of
Brookline.

02:13:36.640 --> 02:13:42.359
Two years ago, Boston Magazine did
Boston's Black 100.

02:13:40.560 --> 02:13:45.799
Four Brookline METCO parents were in
there.

02:13:44.079 --> 02:13:48.600
Not METCO parents, Brookline METCO
parents.

02:13:46.800 --> 02:13:52.520
And so, it is really important to kind of
grasp that piece,

02:13:50.760 --> 02:13:55.400
um, but it's religious, it's cultural,
it's ethnic diversity, it's all those

02:13:53.880 --> 02:14:00.479
things that METCO helps bring to our
district.

02:13:56.840 --> 02:14:00.480
Um, next slide, Betsy.

02:14:00.760 --> 02:14:06.199
This is our organization chart. Um,

02:14:04.119 --> 02:14:09.479
This took a lot of work, not just the
design

02:14:06.199 --> 02:14:12.319
but to get us to this point. Um,

02:14:09.479 --> 02:14:15.719
I saw two of the previous directors,

02:14:12.319 --> 02:14:16.960
Dr. Susie Tulu-Dar and Dr. Keith Lezama.

02:14:15.720 --> 02:14:21.960
