02:15:40.880 --> 02:15:46.400
Thank you. So,

02:15:45.199 --> 02:15:49.839
I can't tell you how often I get asked,
"How do you get into METCO?" or get a

02:15:48.079 --> 02:15:53.360
call saying, "Can you get my child into
METCO?" The answer is almost

02:15:51.680 --> 02:15:57.840
always no. But to explain,

02:15:56.239 --> 02:16:02.440
it is important to know that the METCO
program takes every application.

02:15:59.680 --> 02:16:04.640
I never get an application.

02:16:02.439 --> 02:16:06.399
Then they run their lottery.

02:16:04.640 --> 02:16:10.839
This is changing. This year they had four
separate lotteries.

02:16:08.760 --> 02:16:13.600
The first one was in early December, and

02:16:10.840 --> 02:16:15.840
there are dates and things like that.

02:16:13.600 --> 02:16:19.279
METCO meets with Public Schools of
Brookline enrollment to understand space.

02:16:17.800 --> 02:16:22.679
Brookline MicroSchools ask for referrals
from METCO in late January early.

02:16:20.640 --> 02:16:26.520
In February, we meet about enrollment.
This is mainly about our senior class.

02:16:24.039 --> 02:16:29.399
We wait until after mid-year exams. We see
if students will graduate or not.

02:16:26.520 --> 02:16:33.479
This helps us start planning, but it does
not give us the full picture.

02:16:31.520 --> 02:16:34.840
We talk to the enrollment team. We begin
looking for new students.

02:16:33.479 --> 02:16:38.200
When we get referrals, we look for two
kinds.

02:16:37.079 --> 02:16:42.120
We want referrals for kindergarten
students.

02:16:41.000 --> 02:16:45.599
Mekko has a sibling preference. If a child
has a brother or sister in our district, they can skip the lottery.

02:16:43.879 --> 02:16:48.959
That's how we begin our process.

02:16:45.599 --> 02:16:51.200
After getting referrals, we hold meetings.

02:16:48.959 --> 02:16:54.880
We try to do these in person, but we also
offer Zoom for those who cannot attend.

02:16:52.879 --> 02:16:58.359
We have family intake meetings. I meet
one-on-one with a social worker and the family.

02:16:56.718 --> 02:17:02.200
We collect important information during
these meetings.

02:17:00.120 --> 02:17:04.760
Next, we hold kindergarten day. This is
with the BEEP program.

02:17:02.200 --> 02:17:08.280
Kids sit in on BEEP classes. We want to
see them interact without their parents.

02:17:04.760 --> 02:17:10.519
Then we start placing families into
schools.

02:17:08.280 --> 02:17:14.040
This is like solving a puzzle.

02:17:11.959 --> 02:17:18.400
We want siblings to be in the same school,
but there are limited spaces.

02:17:16.280 --> 02:17:19.760
So, we have to figure out how to fit
everyone into available spots.

02:17:18.399 --> 02:17:23.479
It takes a lot of time, but it is worth
the effort.

02:17:21.000 --> 02:17:25.239
This helps us understand families and
introduce them to MECO.

02:17:23.479 --> 02:17:28.599
We try to place them where they can
succeed.

02:17:25.239 --> 02:17:30.879
This can be challenging, especially for
four- or five-year-olds looking ahead to age 18.

02:17:28.599 --> 02:17:33.920
But we feel we have enough information to
make good choices.

02:17:32.280 --> 02:17:36.879
They came in, they sat in on BEEP classes.
We wanted to see them

02:17:35.079 --> 02:17:39.200
interacting in particular without mom

02:17:36.879 --> 02:17:43.199
and dad next to them.

02:17:39.200 --> 02:17:45.240
And then, we start to place families.

02:17:43.200 --> 02:17:46.559
And that is a bit of a puzzle.

02:17:45.239 --> 02:17:49.599
Cuz again, with siblings, we want to make
sure they're in the same school.

02:17:50.000 --> 02:17:55.519
But we only have spaces so many. So, we
have to like work the puzzle so that we

02:17:53.079 --> 02:17:59.559
can fit the spaces that were provided at
those places.

02:17:57.360 --> 02:18:02.040
And so, you know, that's a it takes a

02:17:59.558 --> 02:18:05.000
long time, and it's um

02:18:02.040 --> 02:18:07.360
I would say well worth it. It helps us

02:18:05.000 --> 02:18:09.519
really get to know families, introduce

02:18:07.360 --> 02:18:12.639
them to ourselves and what MECO is, and

02:18:09.519 --> 02:18:14.440
then place them as best as we can within

02:18:12.638 --> 02:18:19.399
our schools to be successful, which is
hard with a four- or five-year-old

02:18:16.959 --> 02:18:20.718
projecting until they're 18.

02:18:19.399 --> 02:18:24.119
But, we feel like we have enough
information

02:18:21.840 --> 02:18:27.000
to try. So, that's where we go.

02:18:24.120 --> 02:18:29.639
All right. Next slide, please.

02:18:27.000 --> 02:18:32.439
Our budgeting process, the Department of
Elementary and Secondary Education (DESE) has the information for our

02:18:30.920 --> 02:18:37.000
distribution of funds. It's a budget line
in the state budget. They divide

02:18:35.519 --> 02:18:40.319
it up and tell us, DESE tells Brookline
how much state grant

02:18:39.200 --> 02:18:44.599
money we will receive from that budget
line. I found that out last Friday.

02:18:45.120 --> 02:18:49.920
Now, they give us some clues a little bit
ahead of time.

02:18:48.079 --> 02:18:53.760
But, the official information I received
was last Friday, and it might be wrong.

02:18:52.399 --> 02:18:57.399
And I say that because the governor hasn't
signed it yet.

02:18:55.760 --> 02:19:01.879
While they are still negotiating and
discussing everything else,

02:18:59.200 --> 02:19:04.199
I might find out in July that it's a
little less than what we expect,

02:19:02.959 --> 02:19:07.480
or I could find in July that it's a little
more, but that's how it works. We wait

02:19:06.239 --> 02:19:11.239
for them to tell us, and then we set a
budget. The budget is then

02:19:09.239 --> 02:19:12.479
submitted and approved by the Public
Schools of Brookline (PSB) Finance.

02:19:11.239 --> 02:19:16.079
It is signed by the superintendent and
then sent to DESE for approval.

02:19:16.920 --> 02:19:21.840
DESE limits how METCO money can be

02:19:18.879 --> 02:19:24.839
spent. Any money spent must

02:19:21.840 --> 02:19:28.280
directly help Brookline's METCO program
and its

02:19:25.959 --> 02:19:31.840
students. This does not mean it can't help
other Brookline students.

02:19:30.000 --> 02:19:36.760
But, if it only helps Brookline students,
we will face issues. We have faced

02:19:34.079 --> 02:19:41.000
issues before. I think it's really
important to know

02:19:39.360 --> 02:19:45.679
that if I can't show that it's helping
METCO students,

02:19:43.519 --> 02:19:49.200
DESE can say, "You have to change how you
use that money."

02:19:47.000 --> 02:19:53.439
This often happens, especially with
teachers.

02:19:51.959 --> 02:19:57.719
As far as I know, I asked Susie to
research that.

02:19:55.600 --> 02:20:02.199
Since as early as 2011, the Brookline
METCO program has always paid for

02:19:59.319 --> 02:20:04.199
PSB teachers.

02:20:02.200 --> 02:20:06.880
This year there are five teachers, costing
almost

02:20:04.200 --> 02:20:09.720
$600,000.

02:20:06.879 --> 02:20:12.559
That we just pay for. So, I believe we

02:20:09.719 --> 02:20:15.479
have to show which ones apply and directly
help METCO students.

02:20:14.399 --> 02:20:19.920
I think that's really important for us to
know.

