High, but you're MECO for life.

03:07:28.719 --> 03:07:32.679
Kids come back and say, "Oh, Mr. Corthorn,
I got into the party life at

03:07:30.079 --> 03:07:36.120
college. I need help. I need to transfer."
We try to help them settle in

03:07:32.680 --> 03:07:38.520
so they can return and make their parents
happier.

03:07:37.239 --> 03:07:41.880
Sometimes, they are 18, and other times,
they are 22. They say, "I am still figuring it out."

03:07:40.479 --> 03:07:44.719
We have to think about the 80% and the
20%.

03:07:43.159 --> 03:07:48.840
Absolutely. Final question: You have a
strong staff.

03:07:47.440 --> 03:07:51.639
Yes, the MECO (Metco) staff. When I worked
in Brookline, we did not have that many.

03:07:50.559 --> 03:07:53.119
When you look at achievement data, have
you thought about different ways

03:07:52.440 --> 03:07:55.480
to divide the staff's work in the schools
to focus on academics?

03:07:54.879 --> 03:08:00.239
That is what I mean.

03:08:00.040 --> 03:08:06.000
When you say different staff in the
schools, could you clarify?

03:08:04.200 --> 03:08:10.280
The MECO (Metco) advisors. Sure. This is
the first year we have an advisor at every school.

03:08:09.239 --> 03:08:15.520
This was requested by the principals. We
must look at this closely and see what we can do.

03:08:13.959 --> 03:08:20.000
Having an advisor in every school has
helped with attendance issues.

03:08:17.520 --> 03:08:23.959
Some kids only wanted to see the MECO
advisor. If the advisor was not there,

03:08:21.319 --> 03:08:25.360
it was hard to get those kids back on
track.

03:08:23.959 --> 03:08:26.839
I wish I could show you my text messages
from last year to this year.

03:08:25.360 --> 03:08:30.479
The number of principals texting me in an
emergency has gone down a lot.

03:08:28.840 --> 03:08:35.520
Okay.

03:08:33.760 --> 03:08:40.079
first year we've been able to have an
advisor at every school.

03:08:37.319 --> 03:08:43.200
Um and um again, that was something asked
by the principals. So, we're we're

03:08:41.799 --> 03:08:46.520
really going to have to look at that and
see what we can do. I think what it has

03:08:44.920 --> 03:08:51.479
mitigated that I can say with a lot of
confidence

03:08:48.840 --> 03:08:55.840
is having an advisor in every school has
so many that attendance issue

03:08:54.600 --> 03:08:59.680
where where there were kids floating
around in particular, we had kids at

03:08:58.200 --> 03:09:02.680
some schools who only wanted to see the
Meco advisor. Well, if the Meco advisor

03:09:01.479 --> 03:09:05.840
wasn't there because they were at their
other school,

03:09:04.079 --> 03:09:07.399
it was hard to get that kid regulated

03:09:05.840 --> 03:09:11.719
and get back in.

03:09:07.399 --> 03:09:13.639
Um and so, it has I

03:09:11.719 --> 03:09:16.239
I I wish I could show you my text chain
from last year to this year.

03:09:15.864 --> 03:09:20.239
[laughter] The amount of principals who
are texting

03:09:17.959 --> 03:09:24.159
me on a regular basis like in emergency
mode and I have to drive to that school

03:09:22.159 --> 03:09:26.079
has shrunk immensely. Okay.

03:09:24.360 --> 03:09:29.239
But I don't think it's my job. I think
it's the people who are there.

03:09:27.000 --> 03:09:32.760
So, I think that is some easy information
I can gather.

03:09:31.120 --> 03:09:36.880
We will need to look at the information we
have.

03:09:34.760 --> 03:09:41.319
We will see what that means.

03:09:36.879 --> 03:09:44.199
I think it has helped me evaluate things.

03:09:41.319 --> 03:09:46.560
You see, having a person means spending
money.

03:09:46.799 --> 03:09:51.079
That is money that could go to other
things.

03:09:49.239 --> 03:09:55.079
I think one complicated thing in our
system is...

03:09:53.840 --> 03:09:58.319
Please remember, I love our system.

03:09:56.639 --> 03:10:02.639
I believe in Kindergarten through 8th
grade.

03:10:00.399 --> 03:10:06.159
That is why I moved back to put my
children in Kindergarten through 8th.

03:10:04.639 --> 03:10:09.360
I think middle school is hard for kids
going through changes.

03:10:07.680 --> 03:10:13.000
Putting those kids in one place needs some
rethinking.

03:10:09.360 --> 03:10:15.440
What we discovered is that...

03:10:13.000 --> 03:10:18.360
Now we have real contacts that mean
something.

03:10:15.440 --> 03:10:21.720
So, our advisors at those schools know 20
to 30 parents.

03:10:18.360 --> 03:10:23.560
They can say, "Hey, you know, Malcolm
hasn't done his history homework."

03:10:21.719 --> 03:10:26.760
They can help him during win block.

03:10:23.559 --> 03:10:28.799
They say, "Yeah, Dr. Myers will help you
this day because you haven't done your homework."

03:10:26.760 --> 03:10:32.399
You see, it is our first year.

03:10:31.079 --> 03:10:35.600
I need to plan how to build, strengthen
and evaluate things.

03:10:34.000 --> 03:10:38.520
Yeah, I think that's something we need to
keep doing.

03:10:37.120 --> 03:10:41.920
Also, academically, we are still doing
pretty well.

03:10:39.840 --> 03:10:43.799
I showed a picture of a girl who graduated
from Brown University.

03:10:41.920 --> 03:10:47.000
We have two kids in the Posse program
right now.

03:10:45.239 --> 03:10:51.120
This year's group was challenging.

03:10:51.239 --> 03:10:57.639
Still, 80% of our students are going to
college.

03:10:55.000 --> 03:11:00.599
So, I think we are doing alright.

03:10:58.959 --> 03:11:05.920
But we can always do better, and that is
clear.

03:11:04.879 --> 03:11:09.040
Okay, so, Malcolm, thank you.

03:11:07.159 --> 03:11:11.760
Thank you. I appreciate your work.

03:11:10.200 --> 03:11:15.000
THANK YOU. [applause]

