03:40:43.200 --> 03:40:49.440
Um, hi everyone. My name is Zariana
Katicich and Jones and Malcolm Cawthorne

03:40:47.559 --> 03:40:53.159
asked me to speak tonight for METCO and to
support METCO.

03:40:51.879 --> 03:40:57.000
Over the last several months, I have heard
more talk about the

03:40:54.799 --> 03:41:00.840
cost of the METCO program here in
Brookline. While I understand that

03:40:58.959 --> 03:41:04.639
budgets are important, I think we are
asking the wrong question. The question should

03:41:02.719 --> 03:41:07.680
not be how much METCO costs. The question
should be what is the value of

03:41:06.319 --> 03:41:10.200
the community we are building together.

03:41:08.799 --> 03:41:14.440
As someone who grew up in Brookline, I can
tell you that racial

03:41:11.680 --> 03:41:17.800
diversity is not just an idea. It is not
just a number in a report. It is a

03:41:16.159 --> 03:41:21.199
difference between children growing up
alone and children growing up

03:41:19.600 --> 03:41:22.520
learning from each other.

03:41:21.200 --> 03:41:27.200
It is a difference between a school system
that only talks about inclusion

03:41:24.639 --> 03:41:29.479
and one that actually practices it.

03:41:27.200 --> 03:41:32.639
For decades, METCO has brought students
and families to Brookline who have

03:41:31.000 --> 03:41:36.479
enriched our schools, challenged us to
think more broadly, and helped create

03:41:34.799 --> 03:41:40.920
the diverse learning environment that many
people in this town say they value.

03:41:39.159 --> 03:41:44.440
As a Brookline student of color, I know
how important it was to learn alongside

03:41:42.799 --> 03:41:48.720
students from different backgrounds and
experiences. METCO did not only benefit

03:41:47.040 --> 03:41:52.959
the students in the program. It benefited
all of us.

03:41:51.559 --> 03:41:56.759
This is why I find some of the recent
public talks about METCO

03:41:54.760 --> 03:42:00.239
very concerning. At a time when diversity,
equity, and inclusion

03:41:58.360 --> 03:42:03.799
efforts are facing attacks across the
country, including from the Trump

03:42:01.719 --> 03:42:07.840
administration, Brookline keeps saying
that these values are important

03:42:05.399 --> 03:42:10.520
to us. Yet, many members of our community
have seen that as

03:42:08.959 --> 03:42:13.640
Some programs focused on diversity have
received a lot of criticism.

03:42:11.879 --> 03:42:16.760
This includes the decision to cut the
Office of Educational Equity.

03:42:15.120 --> 03:42:20.319
People are also talking about programs
like METCO.

03:42:18.920 --> 03:42:23.680
Some actions make it seem like diversity
efforts are not important.

03:42:21.959 --> 03:42:27.360
Many black and brown families feel this
way.

03:42:25.360 --> 03:42:31.600
Before I finish, I want to mention an
email from Sarah.

03:42:29.879 --> 03:42:35.880
She said that tonight's presentation is
about celebrating METCO.

03:42:33.440 --> 03:42:39.279
I agree that we should honor METCO and not
argue about its budget.

03:42:37.600 --> 03:42:43.960
Malcolm Cawthorn, along with students,
families, and staff, deserve recognition.

03:42:41.879 --> 03:42:46.879
But I think we need to address why people
are speaking up now.

03:42:45.239 --> 03:42:50.119
Celebrating METCO and ensuring it
continues are both important goals.

03:42:48.120 --> 03:42:53.440
These goals go together.

03:42:51.799 --> 03:42:56.880
Our community should know that METCO
should not be cut during tough financial times.

03:42:55.639 --> 03:43:00.399
If we value what METCO brings to
Brookline, we must support it all the time.

03:42:58.479 --> 03:43:03.799
This includes during celebrations and when
making financial decisions.

03:43:02.120 --> 03:43:07.920
METCO is more than just a budget item.

03:43:05.479 --> 03:43:10.879
It shows who we are as a community.

03:43:09.600 --> 03:43:14.519
It shows our commitment to educational
chances for all.

03:43:13.079 --> 03:43:18.360
It also shows that our children learn
better when they are together.

03:43:16.680 --> 03:43:22.000
So tonight, I celebrate METCO.

03:43:20.120 --> 03:43:25.440
I celebrate its students, families, staff,
and its positive effects.

03:43:24.120 --> 03:43:28.600
I ask everyone to keep supporting and
investing in this program.

03:43:26.680 --> 03:43:32.280
It has made Brookline a better, more
diverse, and caring place for years.

03:43:30.159 --> 03:43:35.560
Also, a reminder that tomorrow is
Juneteenth.

03:43:33.799 --> 03:43:38.959
Please come out to celebrate at Cypress
Field at the high school.

03:43:36.760 --> 03:43:42.079
Thank you very much. Enjoy your night.

03:43:40.079 --> 03:43:44.600
Thank you, Zarianna. [applause]

